description:
This is a 15 minute workout called 'Treadmill Climbing Workout  - Scenic Virtual Stair Climb of Chimney Rock in the Blue Ridge Mountains' from the channel Treadily.
The workout falls under Cardio/Treadmill and Cardio/Walking.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
You'll need Treadmill for this workout.
The workout has a The Explorer's Workout and The Meditative Grind vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner and Intermediate.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: This treadmill climbing workout is perfect short runs or walks on an incline. It's a 15 minute climb up and back down North Carolina's Chimney Rock in Blue Ridge Mountains. There are 500 winding stair steps to the top of this huge monolithic Chimney Rock. From there dig deep and head up couple hundred more stairs to reach the top of Exclamation Point.  It's a clear beautiful day, so take in views of up to 75 miles.  When I reached the top my legs were on fire, but you can make this climb as hard as you like or just take this scenic tour from the comfort of your favorite chair. ;-)...
